# pokemon-showdown engine API (verified)

Installed package is `pokemon-showdown` (full Smogon repo), **not** `@pkmn/sim` (same engine).
Format id: `gen9championsvgc2026regma`. Stat points: 66 total, 32/stat (validated in `packTeam`).

## Imports
```ts
const { Battle, PRNG } = require("pokemon-showdown");
const { State } = require("pokemon-showdown/dist/sim/state"); // NOT re-exported from the package root
```

## Drive a battle (sync)
```ts
const b = new Battle({ formatid, seed, strictChoices: true });
b.setPlayer("p1", { name: "p1", team: packTeam(setsA) });
b.setPlayer("p2", { name: "p2", team: packTeam(setsB) });
b.choose("p1", "move 1 1, move 2 -1"); // commits once every acting side has chosen
b.makeChoices();                        // no args = auto-choose; choose("default"/"auto") also auto-picks
```

## Clone + reseed (forking for search)
```ts
const child = State.deserializeBattle(State.serializeBattle(b)); // deep copy, incl. PRNG seed
child.resetRNG(seed);                                            // MUST reseed or chance repeats
```

## Read state (introspect live objects — no protocol-log parsing)
- Phase: `battle.requestState` → `""` (if `battle.ended` → terminal) | `move` | `teampreview` | `switch` (forceSwitch).
- Who acts: sides with `side.activeRequest && !side.activeRequest.wait`.
- Legal options: `side.activeRequest` (raw request: move slots, targets, switches, canMega).
- Terminal: `battle.ended`; winner: `battle.winner` (side name; `""` = tie).
- Per-mon: `side.pokemon[j]` → `.species.id`, `.hp`/`.maxhp`, `.status`, `.ability`, `.item`,
  `.moveSlots`, `.storedStats`, `.boosts`, `.isActive`, `.fainted`, `.volatiles`.

## Output hygiene
Worker stdout = clean JSON responses only. All diagnostics go to **stderr**.
